Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Next to Jubilee Park & the waterfront

CBRE, as the exclusive sales agent, is pleased to present 'Palm Court', 20 Alexandra Road, Glebe. This trophy apartment block commands a prime location beside Jubilee Park and just moments from Rozelle Bay. Comprising 12 studio apartments, the property is just a short drive from Sydney CBD, benefiting from its quiet suburban lifestyle whilst still being surrounded by amenity. 'Palm Courtâ€™ presents a secure investment with a steady cash flow and value add potential. The development of the entire Bays Precinct area, identified by the NSW Government as a State Significant master plan, will underpin capital growth in Glebe and the surrounding suburbs for years to come.

'Palm Court' benefits from the following key attributes:

- Apartment block with 12 studio apartments
- Floor area: 395sqm*
- Land area: 411sqm*
- Potential gross income: $221,316 per annum*
- Strong value add potential through refurbishments
- Adjacent to Jubilee Park and moments to the waterfront at Rozelle Bay
- Short walk to Jubilee Park Light Rail Station with direct services to the city
- Set to benefit from future developments and infrastructure of the Bays Precinct master plan
- Just 2.7km* from Sydney CBD

'Palm Court' will be sold via public auction on Tuesday, 10 September 2019 at 10.30am.

For further information, please contact the exclusive sales agents.

*approximate

Note: All financial figures have been provided by the Vendor. Purchasers are advised to conduct their own independent due diligence.

CBRE are pleased to present 262-264 Glebe Point Road, Glebe.

262-264 Glebe Point Road offers a unique and significant residential conversion opportunity, allowing it to capitalise on Glebe's exclusive, high demand and strong performing residential market. 

The property is ideal for residential developers due to the ability to utilise the building's current improvements and expansive existing gross floor area. 

262-264 Glebe Point Road commands a premium corner location and consists of four storeys plus basement parking, with levels one to three designed around a centralised core. Additionally, the building includes a large 365sqm* rooftop which boasts views of the surrounding district and nearby Sydney CBD.

262-264 Glebe Point Road benefits from the following key attributes:

- Four storey building with basement parking and rooftop breakout space
- Significant conversion potential suitable for residential flat buildings
- Land area of 708sqm* with a gross floor area of 1,685sqm*
- Large floor to ceiling heights and generous light & ventilation
- Premium corner location commanding three street frontages
- Prime location just metres from Rozelle Bay, Jubilee Park,
shops and dining
- Direct light rail and bus services to Sydney CBD
